@TPcoding, not all models can have their inputs resized for example

x = tf.placeholder()
y = tf.reshape(x, (440,1))
... do more stuff

This model needs to have shapes that have 440 elements. you cannot feed a tensor that is length 3 it would have a similar error.

body:
@TPCoding, not all models can have their inputs resized for example

x = tf.placeholder()
y = tf.reshape(x, (440,1))
... do more stuff

This model needs to have shapes that have 440 elements. you cannot feed a tensor that is length 3 it would have a similar error.
